[[firstpython_program">
== Your first Python program in Eclipse
	 Select File -> New -> Project. Select Pydev -> Pydev Project.
	

	
image::pydev10.gif[]
				
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	

	 Create a new project with the name "de.vogella.python.first".
		Select Python version 2.6 and your interpreter.
	

	
image::pydev20.gif[]
				
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	Press finish.

	 Select Window->Open Perspective ->Other. Select the PyDev
		perspective.
	
image::pydev30.gif[]
				
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	

	 Select the "src" folder of your project, right-click it and
		select New
		-> PyDev Modul. Create a module "FirstModule".
	
image::pydev40.gif[]
				
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	

	
image::pydev50.gif[]
				
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	 Create the following source code.

	
		<programlisting>
			<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
				parse="text" href="../examples/first/FirstModule.py[]
----
	
	Right-click your model and select Run As -> Python run.
	
image::pydev60.gif[]
				
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	Congratulations! You created your first (little) Python modul and
		ran it!

